00:30:59,942 --> 00:31:01,569
is deeply insulted by your proposal."

512
00:31:03,279 --> 00:31:04,780
"Go back to Michigan."

513
00:31:09,368 --> 00:31:11,078
"Back to your big, ugly factory."

514
00:31:13,748 --> 00:31:14,999
"Back to your big, ugly factory,

515
00:31:15,082 --> 00:31:16,292
making its ugly, little cars."

516
00:31:24,008 --> 00:31:25,885
"Tell your pigheaded boss that

517
00:31:25,968 --> 00:31:30,973
all his, uh, smug executives
are worthless sons of whores."

518
00:31:33,768 --> 00:31:36,228
Tell him he's not Henry Ford.

519
00:31:38,689 --> 00:31:40,649
He's Henry Ford ll.

520
00:31:43,611 --> 00:31:45,154
I'm starving. Let's go eat.

521
00:32:08,344 --> 00:32:09,637
He played us.

522
00:32:10,596 --> 00:32:12,932
Old Man Enzo had no intention
of selling to us.

523
00:32:14,183 --> 00:32:16,685
He used us to up his price...

524
00:32:17,394 --> 00:32:19,855
embarrass our company
and insult your leadership.

525
00:32:20,731 --> 00:32:22,650
It was a bad idea from the start.

526
00:32:31,534 --> 00:32:33,369
What exactly did he say?

527
00:32:41,585 --> 00:32:43,379
He said Ford makes ugly little cars,

528
00:32:43,462 --> 00:32:44,630
and we make 'em...

529
00:32:45,548 --> 00:32:46,924
in an ugly factory.

530
00:32:48,968 --> 00:32:52,179
He said our executives are sons of whores.

531
00:32:55,933 --> 00:32:57,226
About me?

532
00:32:59,311 --> 00:33:00,729
He called you fat, sir.

533
00:33:02,189 --> 00:33:03,315
And, uh...

534
00:33:03,774 --> 00:33:04,900
pigheaded.

535
00:33:06,193 --> 00:33:07,444
Go on.

536
00:33:08,737 --> 00:33:10,573
He said you're not Henry Ford.

537
00:33:11,699 --> 00:33:13,242
You're Henry Ford ll.

538
00:33:35,890 --> 00:33:39,101
I want the best engineers.

539
00:33:41,228 --> 00:33:42,563
The best drivers.

540
00:33:45,065 --> 00:33:46,734
I don't care what it costs.

541
00:33:50,196 --> 00:33:51,864
We're gonna build a race car.

542
00:33:58,621 --> 00:34:01,290
And we're gonna bury
that goddamn greasy wop

543
00:34:01,373 --> 00:34:05,002
100 feet deep
under the finish line at Le Mans.

544
00:34:06,545 --> 00:34:09,048
And I will be there to watch it.

545
00:34:10,090 --> 00:34:12,051
Here they come. Go, go, go, go.

546
00:34:16,013 --> 00:34:17,014
Assholes.

547
00:34:17,097 --> 00:34:18,265
You're really pathetic.

548
00:34:18,349 --> 00:34:19,266
I'm so sorry, girls.

549
00:34:19,350 --> 00:34:20,684
Charlie!

550
00:34:20,768 --> 00:34:22,770
Quit throwing crackers
at the girls all damn day.

551
00:34:22,853 --> 00:34:24,104
God damn it.

552
00:34:24,188 --> 00:34:25,272
Do I gotta deal with this?

553
00:34:25,356 --> 00:34:26,732
It's already taken care of.

554
00:34:28,108 --> 00:34:32,279
Sorry about that.
So, yeah, 289 cubic inch V8.

555
00:34:32,363 --> 00:34:33,572
Far out.

556
00:34:33,656 --> 00:34:35,491
Extensive rework of AC Ace's front end.

557
00:34:35,574 --> 00:34:37,576
And a stronger rear diff
to handle the torque.

558
00:34:37,660 --> 00:34:39,078
How's she handle a quarter mile?

559
00:34:39,703 --> 00:34:41,914
Well, now, I'm not saying
you should go drag racing,

560
00:34:41,997 --> 00:34:43,582
but a quarter mile's 13.6.

561
00:34:43,666 --> 00:34:44,959
Yeah.

562
00:34:45,042 --> 00:34:46,502
- Is that good?
- Oh, that's real good.

563
00:34:46,585 --> 00:34:49,546
He sold that same car
three times this week.

564
00:34:49,630 --> 00:34:51,882
- You take cash? Is cash okay?
- Cash is okay.

565
00:34:51,966 --> 00:34:54,176
Yeah, mister, you just bought yourself
one hell of a sport car.

566
00:34:54,260 --> 00:34:55,427
All right.

567
00:34:56,929 --> 00:34:59,265
Tell you what, I'm gonna... Phil!

568
00:34:59,348 --> 00:35:00,724
I'm gonna pass you off
to my colleague here.

569
00:35:00,808 --> 00:35:01,976
He gonna take care of you.

570
00:35:02,059 --> 00:35:03,978
- Phil, Wyatt.
- Hello, Wyatt.

571
00:35:04,061 --> 00:35:05,104
I'm gonna steal him for one second.

572
00:35:06,563 --> 00:35:07,815
You take the payment.

573
00:35:07,898 --> 00:35:09,650
Whatever you do,
do not let him take that car.

574
00:35:09,733 --> 00:35:10,985
That's Jeff Blitzer's car.

575
00:35:11,068 --> 00:35:13,070
And Frank Collins' and Steve McQueen's.

576
00:35:13,153 --> 00:35:15,114
Shit. I forgot about McQueen.

577
00:35:18,325 --> 00:35:19,326
Morning.

578
00:35:20,035 --> 00:35:21,036
Can I help you?

579
00:35:22,413 --> 00:35:23,539
Carroll Shelby?

580
00:35:24,748 --> 00:35:25,749
Maybe.

581
00:35:27,334 --> 00:35:29,628
Lee lacocca, Ford Motor.

582
00:35:32,756 --> 00:35:34,383
What's with the wrench?

583
00:35:35,050 --> 00:35:36,844
That? Oh, long story.

584
00:35:37,886 --> 00:35:40,681
We are just going from strength
to strength here, Lee.

585
00:35:41,390 --> 00:35:44,018
Terrific sales,
we're killing it on the track.

586
00:35:44,101 --> 00:35:46,770
Now, I know I owe Ford
for that last batch of engines--

587
00:35:46,854 --> 00:35:49,523
Mr. Shelby, I can assure you
I'm not here for money

588
00:35:49,606 --> 00:35:51,525
that you might owe Ford for spare parts.

589
00:35:52,943 --> 00:35:54,194
You're not?

590
00:35:54,862 --> 00:35:56,322
No, I'm not.

591
00:35:57,406 --> 00:35:58,657
Okay.

592
00:35:58,741 --> 00:36:01,493
I'm here on behalf
of Mr. Ford, Henry Ford ll.

593
00:36:01,577 --> 00:36:04,204
Suppose, um, hypothetically,

594
00:36:04,288 --> 00:36:08,250
that he wanted his company
to win the 24 Hours of Le Mans.

595
00:36:09,626 --> 00:36:12,588
You're one of the only Americans
that's ever done it...

596
00:36:12,671 --> 00:36:13,881
so I'm wondering...

597
00:36:14,798 --> 00:36:15,924
what's it take?

598
00:36:19,470 --> 00:36:20,596
Hypothetically?

599
00:36:21,805 --> 00:36:23,057
Hypothetically.

600
00:36:24,516 --> 00:36:26,185
It takes something money can't buy.

601
00:36:27,561 --> 00:36:28,854
Money can buy speed.

602
00:36:30,564 --> 00:36:32,107
But it isn't about speed, Lee.

603
00:36:33,359 --> 00:36:35,194
It's not just like those other tracks

604
00:36:35,277 --> 00:36:38,155
where all you do is turn
to the left for four hours.

605
00:36:40,949 --> 00:36:42,368
To win that race, you need a car

606
00:36:42,451 --> 00:36:44,661
that's light enough to do 200
on the straightaways

607
00:36:44,745 --> 00:36:47,831
but strong enough to keep that up
for 3,000 miles without a break.

608
00:36:50,167 --> 00:36:51,877
Not just the best car

609
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:53,754
y'all have ever made,
but better than anything

610
00:36:53,837 --> 00:36:55,756
that Enzo Ferrari shows up with that year.

611
00:36:55,839 --> 00:36:57,508
And that just gets you to the green flag.

612
00:36:57,591 --> 00:36:59,259
That's where your problems really start.

613
00:37:01,512 --> 00:37:03,097
Is everything okay?

614
00:37:03,180 --> 00:37:05,099
Go away.

615
00:37:12,564 --> 00:37:14,274
So you're saying it's challenging.

616
00:37:17,027 --> 00:37:18,946
Look, it's not even a track, Lee.

617
00:37:19,822 --> 00:37:21,949
Le Mans is eight and a half
miles of country road.

618
00:37:23,409 --> 00:37:26,787
It's narrow, ungraded, it's rough.

619
00:37:26,870 --> 00:37:29,665
There's no camber on the turns, no rails.

620
00:37:32,459 --> 00:37:34,128
You gotta do that for 24 hours.

621
00:37:36,046 --> 00:37:37,339
Twenty-four hours, Lee.

622
00:37:39,591 --> 00:37:40,717
That means night.

623
00:37:41,427 --> 00:37:44,179
Half that race is in the dark.
You can't see shit.

624
00:37:46,140 --> 00:37:47,975
Cars coming up on you out of nowhere.

625
00:37:49,601 --> 00:37:52,396
Drivers stumbling around
the track, pouring blood.

626
00:37:53,439 --> 00:37:55,149
Maybe one of 'em's your friend. Maybe...

627
00:37:56,150 --> 00:37:57,443
Maybe he's on fire.

628
00:37:59,403 --> 00:38:01,280
You're exhausted, you're hungry...

629
00:38:01,905 --> 00:38:04,408
can't remember your name,
what country you're in.

630
00:38:05,534 --> 00:38:08,745
And all of a sudden, you realize
you're doing 198 on a straight.

631
00:38:12,708 --> 00:38:14,126
And if anything goes wrong...

632
00:38:15,210 --> 00:38:17,880
you blow a gasket, a five-cent washer...

633
00:38:18,547 --> 00:38:20,090
that's it, whole thing's over.

634
00:38:21,175 --> 00:38:22,509
Ferrari wins again.

635
00:38:23,594 --> 00:38:25,762
Just like he won last year
and the year before that.

636
00:38:26,221 --> 00:38:27,473
And the year before that.

637
00:38:31,435 --> 00:38:32,436
Yeah.

638
00:38:33,228 --> 00:38:34,229
It's challenging.

639
00:38:35,814 --> 00:38:37,024
So you don't think...

640
00:38:37,941 --> 00:38:39,401
that Ford Motor Company can build

641
00:38:39,485 --> 00:38:41,570
the greatest race car
the world's ever seen?

642
00:38:41,653 --> 00:38:44,031
You think that we are incapable

643
00:38:44,490 --> 00:38:45,824
of winning an event like that?

644
00:38:46,366 --> 00:38:48,327
Even if we had a brilliant partner?

645
00:38:51,288 --> 00:38:54,750
Even if we wrote a, uh, blank check?

646
00:39:01,465 --> 00:39:04,343
What I'm saying is,
you can't buy a win, Lee.

647
00:39:07,596 --> 00:39:11,141
But maybe you could buy
the guy who gets you a shot.

648
00:39:13,852 --> 00:39:15,270
♪ <i>Have love</i> ♪

649
00:39:16,647 --> 00:39:18,899
♪ <i>Whoa, baby, will travel</i> ♪

650
00:39:21,151 --> 00:39:22,361
♪ <i>Have love</i> ♪

651
00:39:23,862 --> 00:39:25,989
♪ <i>Whoa, baby, will travel...</i> ♪

652
00:39:28,450 --> 00:39:32,829
A new transmission, axles,
shocks all around,

653
00:39:32,913 --> 00:39:35,999
ditch the body and the tires,
you have yourself a contender.

654
00:39:37,376 --> 00:39:39,419
Anything on this beauty that does work?

655
00:39:39,503 --> 00:39:42,130
The mirrors are outstanding.

656
00:39:42,214 --> 00:39:43,465
I saw that walking up.

657
00:39:44,466 --> 00:39:48,595
So, what, you just passing
on an evening stroll?

658
00:39:49,513 --> 00:39:52,099
Actually, Bulldog,
I have a proposition for you.

659
00:39:52,182 --> 00:39:56,144
You're gonna build a car
to beat Old Man Ferrari...

660
00:39:56,228 --> 00:39:57,980
- Yeah.
- ...with Ford?

661
00:39:58,063 --> 00:40:00,274
With a Ford?

662
00:40:00,357 --> 00:40:01,650
Correct.

663
00:40:01,733 --> 00:40:03,652
And how long did you tell them
that you needed?

664
00:40:03,735 --> 00:40:05,279
Two, three hundred years?

665
00:40:05,737 --> 00:40:06,780
Ninety days.

666
00:40:11,034 --> 00:40:13,704
All right, so let's just look
at this for a moment.

667
00:40:14,871 --> 00:40:16,331
And for argument's sake,

668
00:40:16,415 --> 00:40:18,792
let's just forget about
the whole 90-day thing, all right?

669
00:40:18,917 --> 00:40:20,460
So let's just pretend you've got
all the money in the world

670
00:40:20,544 --> 00:40:22,629
and all the time in the world.

671
00:40:22,713 --> 00:40:24,381
- I like the sound of that.
- All right.

672
00:40:24,464 --> 00:40:25,507
So...

673
00:40:26,258 --> 00:40:28,885
you think that Ford
are gonna let you build

674
00:40:29,928 --> 00:40:32,431
the car that you want...

675
00:40:33,140 --> 00:40:34,850
the way you want it?

676
00:40:34,933 --> 00:40:37,644
The Ford Motor Company?

677
00:40:38,937 --> 00:40:40,063
Those guys?

678
00:40:41,398 --> 00:40:42,566
Have you ever been to Detroit?

679
00:40:42,649 --> 00:40:45,652
I mean, they have
floors and floors of lawyers

680
00:40:45,736 --> 00:40:48,822
and millions of marketing guys,
and they're all gonna want to meet you.

681
00:40:48,905 --> 00:40:50,324
All of them are gonna want
to get their photo taken

682
00:40:50,407 --> 00:40:52,492
with the great Carroll Shelby,
and they're gonna kiss your ass

683
00:40:52,576 --> 00:40:54,369
then they're gonna go
back to their lovely offices...

684
00:40:54,911 --> 00:40:56,955
and they're gonna work out
new ways to screw you.

685
00:40:57,039 --> 00:40:59,708
Why? Because they can't help it.

686
00:40:59,791 --> 00:41:01,501
Because they just want
to please their boss

687
00:41:01,585 --> 00:41:04,463
who wants to please his boss
who wants to please his boss.

688
00:41:05,422 --> 00:41:07,591
And they hate themselves for it.

689
00:41:07,674 --> 00:41:09,343
But deep down...

690
00:41:09,426 --> 00:41:12,679
who they hate even more
are guys like you,

691
00:41:12,763 --> 00:41:14,139
because you're not like them,

692
00:41:14,222 --> 00:41:15,807
because you don't think like them,

693
00:41:15,891 --> 00:41:17,643
because you're different.

694
00:41:19,227 --> 00:41:20,854
It's coming straight from the Deuce.

695
00:41:23,523 --> 00:41:26,068
He's serious.
They're gonna put real money behind it.

696
00:41:29,738 --> 00:41:30,906
I'll bet they are.

697
00:41:32,157 --> 00:41:33,492
You know why?

698
00:41:33,575 --> 00:41:36,119
Because someone, and I'm not saying who,

699
00:41:36,203 --> 00:41:41,875
someone has told them that
this is actually possible.

700
00:41:42,334 --> 00:41:43,418
Look...

701
00:41:43,502 --> 00:41:45,212
this Sunday at Cloverfield,

702
00:41:45,295 --> 00:41:46,463
they're launching the new Mustang.

703
00:41:46,546 --> 00:41:48,131
They're gonna announce the race program.

704
00:41:49,508 --> 00:41:50,592
Just come on by.

705
00:41:52,886 --> 00:41:55,472
Come take a look. Listen to my speech.

706
00:41:56,181 --> 00:41:57,099
I'm making a speech.

707
00:41:57,641 --> 00:41:59,518
Bring Peter. He'll love it.

708
00:42:01,144 --> 00:42:03,063
All right, Shel.

709
00:42:05,399 --> 00:42:06,858
See you Sunday.

710
00:42:10,153 --> 00:42:11,446
Whoa.

711
00:42:12,239 --> 00:42:15,033
Dad, look at that.

712
00:42:16,201 --> 00:42:17,369
Huh.

713
00:42:18,829 --> 00:42:21,373
The Ford Mustang. What do you think?

714
00:42:24,876 --> 00:42:26,712
I think it's a secretary's car.

715
00:42:28,630 --> 00:42:29,881
I like it.

716
00:42:31,758 --> 00:42:32,759
Oh.

717
00:42:32,843 --> 00:42:34,428
Excu... Excuse me.

718
00:42:36,346 --> 00:42:37,723
Would you, would you not do that?

719
00:42:38,432 --> 00:42:40,392
Oh. Sorry.

720
00:42:43,687 --> 00:42:46,231
Oh, er, is this, is this your son?

721
00:42:47,107 --> 00:42:48,525
Yes, it is.

722
00:42:48,608 --> 00:42:51,027
Would you ask him to keep
his hands off the paintwork?

723
00:42:51,737 --> 00:42:54,322
No, no, no, Peter.
You're okay. Who are you?

724
00:42:54,990 --> 00:42:55,949
Leo Beebe,

725
00:42:56,032 --> 00:42:57,701
senior executive vice president,
Ford Motor Company.

726
00:42:57,784 --> 00:42:58,827
Ah.

727
00:42:58,910 --> 00:43:01,079
I'm responsible for the launch
of the Mustang.

728
00:43:01,163 --> 00:43:03,915
Ah! At least now we know
who's responsible.

729
00:43:03,999 --> 00:43:05,041
Don't get me wrong, Lenny.

730
00:43:05,125 --> 00:43:08,044
- Leo.
- It looks fantastic.

731
00:43:08,128 --> 00:43:11,381
But inside, it's a lump of lard
dressed up to fool the public.

732
00:43:11,465 --> 00:43:13,425
My advice is,

733
00:43:13,508 --> 00:43:16,720
lose the inline-six
and that idiotic three-speed,

734
00:43:16,803 --> 00:43:20,307
shorten the wheelbase,
somehow lose half a ton,

735
00:43:20,390 --> 00:43:21,641
and lower the price.

736
00:43:21,725 --> 00:43:22,726
Dad.

737
00:43:22,809 --> 00:43:25,437
But even then,
I'd still choose a Chevy Chevelle.

738
00:43:26,605 --> 00:43:29,149
And that's a fucking terrible car.

739
00:43:30,650 --> 00:43:32,152
<i>How are we doing up there, Steve?</i>

740
00:43:32,861 --> 00:43:34,404
There's Cloverfield, Mr. Shelby.

741
00:43:35,197 --> 00:43:36,573
Oh, yeah.

742
00:43:37,491 --> 00:43:39,284
You mind if I take a shot at the landing?

743
00:43:39,367 --> 00:43:40,368
Uh...

744
00:43:40,452 --> 00:43:41,578
No, no, no. I mean it.

745
00:43:41,661 --> 00:43:44,664
- I flew B-29s out of San Antone in '44.
- You're kidding.

746
00:43:45,165 --> 00:43:46,917
- I did.
- Okay.

747
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:48,210
Carroll, what are you doing?

748
00:43:48,293 --> 00:43:49,795
- Does he know how to fly?
- Carroll.

749
00:43:49,878 --> 00:43:52,631
I had an instructor tell me, he said...

750
00:43:52,714 --> 00:43:54,966
Don, I would say it's probably
a good time to buckle up.

751
00:43:55,050 --> 00:43:56,843
"...do everybody a favor,
stay on the ground."

752
00:43:58,136 --> 00:43:59,429
That's a true story.

753
00:43:59,513 --> 00:44:00,764
- Oh, no.
- Oh, shit.

754
00:44:00,847 --> 00:44:02,516
- God damn it.
- Here we go.

755
00:44:02,599 --> 00:44:05,811
<i>This is the car
you never expected from Detroit.</i>

756
00:44:08,814 --> 00:44:11,316
All right. Let's go.

757
00:44:13,235 --> 00:44:14,694
Not staying, Ken?

758
00:44:15,362 --> 00:44:17,739
Ah, it's a bloody pig in a poke, isn't it?

759
00:44:17,823 --> 00:44:19,115
Oh, here they come now.

760
00:44:23,870 --> 00:44:26,456
- Wait. Are they crashing?
- Oh, Lord.

761
00:44:26,540 --> 00:44:28,041
Who's the pilot?

762
00:44:28,124 --> 00:44:29,751
My guess, Peter...

763
00:44:33,129 --> 00:44:34,339
it's someone we know.

764
00:44:35,841 --> 00:44:36,925
<i>Everything all right up there?</i>

765
00:44:37,676 --> 00:44:39,177
Oh, no.

766
00:44:39,261 --> 00:44:40,470
- No!
- Hang on.

767
00:44:40,554 --> 00:44:43,139
Oh, shit. Shit. Shit. Shit.

768
00:44:43,223 --> 00:44:46,726
<i>Shit. Shit. Shit.</i>

769
00:44:46,810 --> 00:44:48,562
