01:14:31,009 --> 01:14:32,510
- Ow!
- You all right?

1272
01:14:32,594 --> 01:14:33,845
Shit!

1273
01:14:35,472 --> 01:14:36,890
Now you're gonna get it.

1274
01:14:38,683 --> 01:14:40,518
Come here.

1275
01:14:43,021 --> 01:14:44,105
Done.

1276
01:14:49,277 --> 01:14:50,362
Mollie, darling.

1277
01:14:51,154 --> 01:14:52,197
Yes, love?

1278
01:14:52,697 --> 01:14:54,115
Can I get a fizzy pop, please?

1279
01:14:55,533 --> 01:14:56,576
Yes, love.

1280
01:14:58,411 --> 01:14:59,746
You want one, too, Shelby?

1281
01:15:00,246 --> 01:15:02,165
- No. No.
- Uh, yes, please, Mollie.

1282
01:15:02,248 --> 01:15:04,042
No. He can get his own.

1283
01:15:04,542 --> 01:15:05,794
Just for me, please.

1284
01:15:12,759 --> 01:15:13,927
How long has that been?

1285
01:15:15,136 --> 01:15:17,013
Oh, it's gotta be three
or four years, at least.

1286
01:15:17,097 --> 01:15:19,349
Right. Riverside.

1287
01:15:19,432 --> 01:15:22,102
Yeah. SCCA Divisional Championship.

1288
01:15:22,727 --> 01:15:23,895
You broke my finger.

1289
01:15:25,980 --> 01:15:29,818
What's that nippy bloody thing

1290
01:15:30,276 --> 01:15:31,736
you do under the arm, that thing?

1291
01:15:31,820 --> 01:15:33,488
Yeah. I call that the Llama Bite.

1292
01:15:33,571 --> 01:15:36,199
You name it?

1293
01:15:36,282 --> 01:15:38,660
Where'd you learn that? The Girl Scouts?

1294
01:15:38,743 --> 01:15:40,829
- What? You wanna go again?
- Here you go.

1295
01:15:42,205 --> 01:15:43,331
You're an angel.

1296
01:15:43,415 --> 01:15:44,499
Thank you.

1297
01:15:44,582 --> 01:15:45,709
My pleasure.

1298
01:15:46,751 --> 01:15:49,212
Right. Well, I'm about to go
to the grocery store.

1299
01:15:49,295 --> 01:15:50,839
Anything you think you'll need?

1300
01:15:51,589 --> 01:15:53,508
Um, ice cream.

1301
01:15:54,634 --> 01:15:56,344
Ice cream would be good and, uh...

1302
01:15:57,220 --> 01:15:58,263
bread.

1303
01:15:59,556 --> 01:16:00,724
Right.

1304
01:16:00,807 --> 01:16:02,308
No, I'm good. Thank you.

1305
01:16:03,226 --> 01:16:05,353
Thanks, Moll.

1306
01:16:05,437 --> 01:16:06,938
You still take those for your ticker?

1307
01:16:07,522 --> 01:16:09,524
Only 'cause they're so delicious.

1308
01:16:09,607 --> 01:16:12,485
- Up yours.
- Oh, go to hell.

1309
01:16:20,577 --> 01:16:22,579
Come on. Giddy-up.
Giddy-up. Giddy-up. Giddy-up!

1310
01:16:38,553 --> 01:16:41,097
Phil! Here's the one for you, mate.

1311
01:16:41,181 --> 01:16:42,474
Dino, come here.

1312
01:17:00,867 --> 01:17:03,703
- Well?
- There's still lag when I hit the gas.

1313
01:17:03,787 --> 01:17:05,288
Let's get rid of the vacuum secondaries.

1314
01:17:05,371 --> 01:17:06,748
Charlie, get a Holley carb.

1315
01:17:06,831 --> 01:17:08,625
We're gonna rebuild the throttle assembly.

1316
01:17:08,708 --> 01:17:10,168
Three weeks to Daytona,

1317
01:17:10,251 --> 01:17:13,129
and it still feels
like a bag of squirrels.

1318
01:17:13,213 --> 01:17:14,255
Brake heat.

1319
01:17:14,839 --> 01:17:16,674
That's a whole different ball game.

1320
01:17:16,758 --> 01:17:18,968
All right, Petey,
let's go for that ride.

1321
01:17:27,811 --> 01:17:28,937
What are you doing?

1322
01:17:30,647 --> 01:17:32,106
You see that crack?

1323
01:17:32,190 --> 01:17:33,733
That's my marker for turn eight.

1324
01:17:36,861 --> 01:17:38,154
What, to slow down?

1325
01:17:39,239 --> 01:17:42,200
Uh, brush the brakes and downshift.

1326
01:17:44,369 --> 01:17:46,621
But you'll be going 150 miles an hour.

1327
01:17:47,580 --> 01:17:48,790
Yeah.

1328
01:17:48,873 --> 01:17:50,583
So how do you see it?

1329
01:17:50,667 --> 01:17:53,419
You're going fast,
but as the car speeds up...

1330
01:17:54,128 --> 01:17:56,381
everything else slows down.

1331
01:17:56,464 --> 01:17:58,007
You don't do that.

1332
01:17:59,050 --> 01:18:00,969
You do this. Right?

1333
01:18:01,052 --> 01:18:02,762
And then you see everything.

1334
01:18:05,598 --> 01:18:07,392
Do you set other markers?

1335
01:18:07,475 --> 01:18:09,602
Indeed I do.

1336
01:18:11,271 --> 01:18:12,438
Lots of them.

1337
01:18:14,566 --> 01:18:18,862
Yeah, 'cause you can't just push
the car hard the whole way, right?

1338
01:18:18,945 --> 01:18:21,656
That's right. You have
to be kind to the car.

1339
01:18:21,739 --> 01:18:25,910
You feel the poor thing
groaning underneath you.

1340
01:18:26,911 --> 01:18:30,790
If you're gonna push a piece
of machinery to the limit

1341
01:18:30,874 --> 01:18:32,625
and expect it to hold together,

1342
01:18:32,709 --> 01:18:36,880
you have to have some sense
of where that limit is.

1343
01:18:39,799 --> 01:18:40,800
Look out there.

1344
01:18:41,968 --> 01:18:44,888
Out there is the perfect lap.

1345
01:18:47,223 --> 01:18:48,391
No mistakes.

1346
01:18:49,225 --> 01:18:51,394
Every gear change, every corner...

1347
01:18:53,146 --> 01:18:54,188
perfect.

1348
01:18:55,857 --> 01:18:57,025
You see it?

1349
01:19:01,237 --> 01:19:02,405
I think so.

1350
01:19:04,449 --> 01:19:05,867
Most people can't.

1351
01:19:07,327 --> 01:19:09,996
Most people don't even know
it's out there, but it is.

1352
01:19:12,373 --> 01:19:13,541
It's there.

1353
01:19:16,628 --> 01:19:17,921
You want some ice cream?

1354
01:19:20,632 --> 01:19:21,883
- Yeah.
- All right.

1355
01:19:22,967 --> 01:19:24,010
Come on, then.

1356
01:19:24,719 --> 01:19:26,220
Do you know what this marker is?

1357
01:19:26,304 --> 01:19:27,388
- What?
- That one.

1358
01:19:27,472 --> 01:19:28,848
Pull my finger. You'll find out.

1359
01:19:51,037 --> 01:19:53,122
How much longer before he comes in?

1360
01:19:53,206 --> 01:19:55,667
Uh, well, we change drivers
every four hours,

1361
01:19:55,750 --> 01:19:57,460
- so about 10 minutes.
- No, <i>hang on.</i>

1362
01:19:57,543 --> 01:20:00,088
You're saying Beebe
is 100 percent in charge now?

1363
01:20:00,171 --> 01:20:02,048
<i>Yes, and he wants Miles gone.</i>

1364
01:20:02,840 --> 01:20:04,759
Look, it is personal with this guy.

1365
01:20:04,842 --> 01:20:06,844
And, yes, he has the leverage
to stick it to you.

1366
01:20:06,928 --> 01:20:08,596
<i>He and the Deuce
are flying there tomorrow.</i>

1367
01:20:08,680 --> 01:20:09,764
He's gonna tell you in person.

1368
01:20:09,847 --> 01:20:11,099
Now, all he is hoping for

1369
01:20:11,182 --> 01:20:12,725
- is that you lose your cool.
- <i>Uh-huh.</i>

1370
01:20:12,809 --> 01:20:14,435
<i>It's time to let this go.</i>

1371
01:20:14,519 --> 01:20:15,812
You cannot destroy the whole thing.

1372
01:20:15,895 --> 01:20:16,980
Not for one goddamn guy.

1373
01:20:17,063 --> 01:20:19,023
- Sure, I can.
- <i>Well, why?</i>

1374
01:20:19,107 --> 01:20:21,609
'Cause while we're here talking,
he's out there getting it done.

1375
01:20:29,242 --> 01:20:31,285
Oh, shit!

1376
01:20:32,787 --> 01:20:34,247
He's got brake fade.

1377
01:20:41,754 --> 01:20:42,755
Ease off!

1378
01:20:53,182 --> 01:20:54,142
<i>Carroll?</i>

1379
01:20:54,517 --> 01:20:55,601
- Get him out!
- Peter!

1380
01:20:55,685 --> 01:20:57,478
Go on. Go inside.

1381
01:20:57,562 --> 01:20:58,604
Just stay there.

1382
01:20:58,688 --> 01:21:00,064
- Get Ken!
- Ken!

1383
01:21:00,148 --> 01:21:01,357
Get him out!

1384
01:21:03,276 --> 01:21:04,277
There he is!

1385
01:21:04,360 --> 01:21:05,319
Ken!

1386
01:21:05,403 --> 01:21:06,571
I can see him.

1387
01:21:13,077 --> 01:21:14,287
- Ken!
- Come on.

1388
01:21:21,085 --> 01:21:22,170
The brakes.

1389
01:21:31,846 --> 01:21:34,766
Let's just rip out
the damn engine. All right?

1390
01:21:34,849 --> 01:21:37,518
We can't use it if we can't stop.

1391
01:21:37,602 --> 01:21:39,062
You know,
the brakes would last longer

1392
01:21:39,145 --> 01:21:40,646
if we slowed down a bit.

1393
01:21:41,022 --> 01:21:43,316
Wouldn't that defeat the whole
purpose of the extra power?

1394
01:21:44,192 --> 01:21:46,611
You know, I thought the whole point
was to win the damned race.

1395
01:21:47,570 --> 01:21:49,655
Maybe we could design
a new assembly.

1396
01:21:49,739 --> 01:21:53,326
Instead of swapping out
the pads in the pits...

1397
01:21:53,868 --> 01:21:56,454
swap out the entire braking system.

1398
01:21:56,537 --> 01:21:57,914
Rotors included.

1399
01:21:58,664 --> 01:21:59,874
Put in a fresh one.

1400
01:21:59,957 --> 01:22:02,960
Wait, wait, wait, Pops,
are we allowed to do that?

1401
01:22:03,044 --> 01:22:06,005
I don't know. I don't read French.

1402
01:22:07,965 --> 01:22:12,678
Well, brakes are "a part"
like any other, right?

1403
01:22:12,762 --> 01:22:15,223
We are allowed to change parts.

1404
01:22:15,306 --> 01:22:17,183
Yes.
Will we have time to do that?

1405
01:22:17,266 --> 01:22:18,726
I don't know yet, Charlie.

1406
01:22:19,519 --> 01:22:22,313
- I'm gonna take him home.
- All right.

1407
01:22:22,396 --> 01:22:24,607
- Sort this shit out.
- I will.

1408
01:22:34,200 --> 01:22:36,410
Have you ever been on fire?

1409
01:22:38,871 --> 01:22:42,291
Uh, well, no, it's never happened to me.

1410
01:22:47,421 --> 01:22:49,799
The suit's flameproof, see?

1411
01:22:49,882 --> 01:22:51,300
It, uh, keeps heat out.

1412
01:22:52,301 --> 01:22:53,302
Yeah.

1413
01:22:55,096 --> 01:22:58,724
But Lewis-Evans burned to death
in the Moroccan Grand Prix.

1414
01:22:58,850 --> 01:23:00,810
He had a flameproof suit on.

1415
01:23:02,145 --> 01:23:04,897
Mm-hmm. Yeah, but, um...

1416
01:23:07,942 --> 01:23:09,360
See, he got stuck.

1417
01:23:09,443 --> 01:23:10,736
He couldn't breathe.

1418
01:23:12,113 --> 01:23:15,324
So, as long as you get out
of the car, you're okay.

1419
01:23:19,579 --> 01:23:21,038
Dad got out.

1420
01:23:22,456 --> 01:23:23,958
- He sure did.
- Peter!

1421
01:23:28,045 --> 01:23:29,130
Bye.

1422
01:23:30,214 --> 01:23:31,340
See ya.

1423
01:23:34,135 --> 01:23:35,595
- You all right?
- Yeah.

1424
01:23:36,888 --> 01:23:38,014
What's wrong with you?

1425
01:23:39,140 --> 01:23:42,894
And don't be telling me brakes
or me almost kicking the bucket out there.

1426
01:23:42,977 --> 01:23:45,104
It's something to do
with the suits, isn't it?

1427
01:23:47,648 --> 01:23:49,150
It's under control.

1428
01:23:49,233 --> 01:23:50,610
What is it?

1429
01:23:50,693 --> 01:23:52,236
You know how we talked about
how you do your thing,

1430
01:23:52,320 --> 01:23:53,446
I do my thing?

1431
01:23:53,529 --> 01:23:54,822
- This is my thing.
- Really, Shel--

1432
01:23:54,906 --> 01:23:56,199
Just trust me, Ken.

1433
01:23:57,074 --> 01:23:58,242
You got a plan?

1434
01:23:59,160 --> 01:24:00,244
Absolutely.

1435
01:24:00,912 --> 01:24:01,913
It a good one?

1436
01:24:02,914 --> 01:24:04,290
It's high risk.

1437
01:24:04,373 --> 01:24:05,458
How high risk?

1438
01:24:05,541 --> 01:24:06,876
Extremely high risk.

1439
01:24:08,836 --> 01:24:10,087
Well, that's something.

1440
01:24:11,047 --> 01:24:12,882
- Glad we had this talk.
- Anytime.

1441
01:24:25,228 --> 01:24:27,521
Mr. Ford, this is a surprise.

1442
01:24:28,564 --> 01:24:30,942
Apologies for the unannounced
intrusion, Mr. Shelby,

1443
01:24:31,025 --> 01:24:34,320
but when a man pays $9 million
for an automobile,

1444
01:24:34,403 --> 01:24:36,239
he ought to at least be able to see it.

1445
01:24:36,322 --> 01:24:37,823
Well, that sounds reasonable enough.

1446
01:24:37,907 --> 01:24:39,742
Uh, Shelby, could I have a word?

1447
01:24:39,825 --> 01:24:41,077
Sure.

1448
01:24:41,160 --> 01:24:42,954
- In private?
- Uh, yeah.

1449
01:24:43,037 --> 01:24:44,580
That would be preferable.

1450
01:24:44,664 --> 01:24:45,873
All right. Hey, Phil.

1451
01:24:45,957 --> 01:24:47,541
You wanna take care of Mr. Ford here?

1452
01:24:47,625 --> 01:24:49,252
Mr. Ford, that's Phil Remington.

1453
01:24:49,335 --> 01:24:50,378
Of course.

1454
01:24:50,461 --> 01:24:51,504
Come up to my office, Leo.

1455
01:24:51,587 --> 01:24:52,755
- Pleasure to meet you, sir.
- Phil.

1456
01:24:52,838 --> 01:24:54,799
Give you a little tour of your car.

1457
01:24:55,841 --> 01:24:58,678
We, uh, took out your 289 small block...

1458
01:24:59,428 --> 01:25:01,722
and put in a 4277-liter.

1459
01:25:04,558 --> 01:25:06,978
Uh, firstly, I want to just clear the air.

1460
01:25:07,061 --> 01:25:09,313
I hope that whatever disagreements

1461
01:25:09,397 --> 01:25:11,232
between us can just be chalked up...

1462
01:25:11,983 --> 01:25:14,610
to natural red-bloodedness
in the heat of battle.

1463
01:25:14,694 --> 01:25:17,321
Oh, I appreciate that, Leo. Truly, I do.

1464
01:25:19,073 --> 01:25:23,619
It falls on me, Shelby, to inform you
that I have been appointed

1465
01:25:23,703 --> 01:25:26,455
overall executive director
of the racing program.

1466
01:25:28,040 --> 01:25:31,544
Now, I do hope that this
won't be a problem between us.

1467
01:25:32,586 --> 01:25:34,630
Well, I assure you, Leo, it will not.

1468
01:25:45,016 --> 01:25:46,100
Hey, Carroll...

1469
01:25:46,726 --> 01:25:47,727
Carroll!

1470
01:25:47,810 --> 01:25:50,229
And what is that top speed
with the, uh, 427?

1471
01:25:50,313 --> 01:25:52,148
Well, why don't we take it for a spin?

1472
01:25:52,231 --> 01:25:53,733
- What?
- Yeah, go on, Mr. Ford.

1473
01:25:53,816 --> 01:25:56,193
- Hop on in. Go on.
- You want me to...

1474
01:25:56,277 --> 01:25:58,321
Just see
what $9 million feels like.

1475
01:25:58,404 --> 01:26:00,740
Hey!

1476
01:26:00,823 --> 01:26:02,116
God...

1477
01:26:05,703 --> 01:26:06,787
Open the door!

1478
01:26:06,871 --> 01:26:08,414
Hey, open the door!

1479
01:26:09,081 --> 01:26:10,791
Open the door!

1480
01:26:13,085 --> 01:26:15,880
Just hold me right there,
and you take my hand.

1481
01:26:17,715 --> 01:26:20,593
Oh, God. I sat on my nuts.

1482
01:26:20,676 --> 01:26:22,428
We're gonna build the next one
for comfort. Don't you worry.

1483
01:26:31,354 --> 01:26:32,813
Open the door.

1484
01:26:32,897 --> 01:26:34,231
Sorry, sir, if you just give me a moment.

1485
01:26:34,315 --> 01:26:35,399
- Open the door.
- It's a sticky one.

1486
01:26:35,483 --> 01:26:37,234
You ready?

1487
01:26:37,318 --> 01:26:38,944
The name on the middle
of that steering wheel

1488
01:26:39,028 --> 01:26:41,364
should tell you that I was
born ready, Shelby. Hit it.

1489
01:26:41,447 --> 01:26:43,574
Attaboy.

1490
01:26:45,701 --> 01:26:48,496
Whoa! It's got a little kick, doesn't it?

1491
01:26:48,913 --> 01:26:50,831
- Open this door.
- Oh, there we go.

1492
01:26:50,915 --> 01:26:52,958
Good God, Mr. Beebe. You okay, sir?

1493
01:26:55,044 --> 01:26:57,254
Whoa! Oh, my God!

1494
01:26:58,506 --> 01:27:01,092
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

1495
01:27:04,887 --> 01:27:06,389
Yeah, baby.

1496
01:27:06,472 --> 01:27:09,016
Yeah, baby.

1497
01:27:12,186 --> 01:27:16,565
It's about right now the uninitiated
have a tendency to soil themselves.

1498
01:27:23,531 --> 01:27:26,242
Oh, my God! Whoa!

1499
01:27:26,242 --> 01:27:56,242
<b>Subtitle 
 www.movieddl.me</b>

1500
01:28:02,736 --> 01:28:03,863
Mr. Ford...

1501
01:28:07,825 --> 01:28:09,285
You okay?

1502
01:28:12,663 --> 01:28:13,706
Mr. Ford...

1503
01:28:14,457 --> 01:28:15,583
you all right?

1504
01:28:15,666 --> 01:28:16,917
I had no idea.

1505
01:28:19,587 --> 01:28:20,921
I had no idea.

1506
01:28:23,924 --> 01:28:25,301
I wish my daddy...

1507
01:28:25,801 --> 01:28:27,386
he were alive to see this.

1508
01:28:27,761 --> 01:28:30,306
To feel this.

1509
01:28:32,224 --> 01:28:34,143
Now, this is not a machine
just anybody can get in

1510
01:28:34,226 --> 01:28:35,436
and easily control.

1511
01:28:35,519 --> 01:28:36,770
Absolutely not.

1512
01:28:37,605 --> 01:28:38,689
I had no idea.

1513
01:28:38,772 --> 01:28:40,024
Now, you wanna win Le Mans.

1514
01:28:40,983 --> 01:28:43,903
If you really wanna take first place,
Ken Miles is the man to do it.

1515
01:28:53,162 --> 01:28:54,497
Good timing.

1516
01:28:54,580 --> 01:28:55,664
<i>Now, he knows this car</i>

1517
01:28:55,748 --> 01:28:57,208
because he helped me build it.

1518
01:28:58,751 --> 01:29:03,088
Shelby, you know I've already
appointed Leo Beebe director of racing.

1519
01:29:03,172 --> 01:29:05,007
Which is exactly why I'm talking to you.

1520
01:29:06,175 --> 01:29:08,761
Now, you let Ken Miles race Daytona.

1521
01:29:09,553 --> 01:29:10,846
If he wins...

1522
01:29:11,889 --> 01:29:13,474
he gets to drive Le Mans.

1523
01:29:16,143 --> 01:29:17,353
And if he doesn't?

1524
01:29:18,354 --> 01:29:21,941
Ford Motor Company gets full ownership
of Shelby American.

1525
01:29:22,024 --> 01:29:23,484
Lock, stock, and brand.

1526
01:29:23,567 --> 01:29:24,610
Forever.

1527
01:29:27,988 --> 01:29:30,741
<i>We're in
hour six at the Daytona 24,</i>

1528
01:29:30,824 --> 01:29:33,410
<i>and Fords are dominating the leader board.</i>

1529
01:29:34,161 --> 01:29:37,248
<i>Shelby American's Ken Miles
holds a narrow lead</i>

1530
01:29:37,331 --> 01:29:40,125
<i>over the Holman-Moody Ford
driven by Walt Hansgen.</i>

1531
01:29:41,252 --> 01:29:43,420
I don't bloody think so, Walt.

1532
01:30:02,064 --> 01:30:05,109
Oh, this race is not just
a test of our cars,

1533
01:30:05,192 --> 01:30:06,569
but also our teams.

1534
01:30:06,652 --> 01:30:08,696
As you know, we have
a second team out there today.

1535
01:30:08,779 --> 01:30:10,364
- Holman-Moody.
- That's right.

1536
01:30:11,115 --> 01:30:14,076
<i>Number 95, Hansgen,
blisters through the front tri-oval</i>

1537
01:30:14,159 --> 01:30:16,161
<i>while closing in on Ken Miles.</i>

1538
01:30:16,245 --> 01:30:17,663
Walt's pushing her too fast.

1539
01:30:17,746 --> 01:30:20,040
He's pushing 7,000 RPM.

1540
01:30:20,124 --> 01:30:21,542
Hey, get the EZ sign out there.

1541
01:30:21,625 --> 01:30:23,377
Come on. Move. Do it now.

1542
01:30:23,460 --> 01:30:27,214
Every one of these GTs out there today
is under my direct supervision.

1543
01:30:27,298 --> 01:30:30,301
And of course the supervision
of Henry Ford ll.

1544
01:30:30,384 --> 01:30:33,220
The drivers, the speed, the strategy...

1545
01:30:33,804 --> 01:30:36,640
even the RPMs are determined by us.

1546
01:30:40,477 --> 01:30:42,062
<i>Ken Miles
is locked in a pitched battle</i>

1547
01:30:42,146 --> 01:30:45,024
<i>with Hansgen as they pass the grandstand.</i>

1548
01:30:48,319 --> 01:30:51,155
<i>Hansgen is taking a run
at Miles entering turn one.</i>

1549
01:30:51,238 --> 01:30:52,531
<i>Miles is boxed in.</i>

1550
01:30:52,615 --> 01:30:56,869
<i>Hansgen slips by and takes the lead
approaching the infield chicane.</i>

1551
01:31:06,795 --> 01:31:07,921
Cor blimey!

1552
01:31:08,005 --> 01:31:09,006
Did you see that?

1553
01:31:09,590 --> 01:31:10,758
<i>The caution flag is out.</i>

1554
01:31:17,431 --> 01:31:19,975
Still racing. Hey, we are still racing.

1555
01:31:20,059 --> 01:31:21,060
Come on, guys, let's go!

1556
01:31:21,143 --> 01:31:22,144
Let's go. Move it.

1557
01:31:22,227 --> 01:31:23,187
He's coming in.

1558
01:31:24,229 --> 01:31:26,357
Let's go, let's go, guys. Come on.

1559
01:31:26,440 --> 01:31:27,816
Go, tires up.

1560
01:31:27,900 --> 01:31:29,526
Here, right here.
Let's go. Let's go. Move it.

1561
01:31:29,610 --> 01:31:31,487
- Fuel flying in.
- Breaker bar!

1562
01:31:31,570 --> 01:31:33,113
- We're good.
- It all checked out.

1563
01:31:33,197 --> 01:31:34,907
- 36. 38.
- Go! Go!

1564
01:31:34,990 --> 01:31:37,409
Hansgen is right up our arse.

1565
01:31:37,493 --> 01:31:39,161
If I can just get
outta the pit ahead of him...

1566
01:31:39,244 --> 01:31:41,872
She's running hot,
but I think she'll hold.

1567
01:31:41,955 --> 01:31:43,415
- Fuel's low.
- Bring up the scoop.

1568
01:31:43,499 --> 01:31:44,583
She's hot.

1569
01:31:47,002 --> 01:31:48,879
Hey there, Walt. Good to see you.

1570
01:31:48,962 --> 01:31:51,882
Yeah, after I get out of this pit, Shelby,
it's the last time you will.

1571
01:31:51,965 --> 01:31:52,966
Oh, don't worry.

1572
01:31:53,050 --> 01:31:54,176
We got rearview mirrors.

1573
01:31:55,719 --> 01:31:57,388
What happened to that Mustang he took out?

1574
01:31:58,138 --> 01:31:59,598
Don't know yet.

1575
01:31:59,682 --> 01:32:02,476
I can push her harder than six, Shel.

1576
01:32:02,559 --> 01:32:04,770
- I can feel it.
- Uh-huh.

1577
01:32:08,524 --> 01:32:12,403
Hey, how come these guys pit
so much faster than we do?

1578
01:32:12,486 --> 01:32:16,031
They got a goddamn
NASCAR crew, that's why.

1579
01:32:16,115 --> 01:32:17,783
- No shit?
- No shit.

1580
01:32:18,409 --> 01:32:20,119
Go! Go, come on.

1581
01:32:21,578 --> 01:32:23,288
We're clear, we're clear.

1582
01:32:23,372 --> 01:32:24,540
Goddamn NASCAR crew.

1583
01:32:24,623 --> 01:32:26,166
Go, go, go!

1584
01:32:26,709 --> 01:32:28,293
Guys, they've already left.

1585
01:32:31,088 --> 01:32:32,214
Hello?

1586
01:32:32,297 --> 01:32:34,174
<i>There's my Mollie. Hello.</i>

1587
01:32:34,883 --> 01:32:36,009
Hiya, love.

1588
01:32:36,093 --> 01:32:37,928
- Mom? Mom?
- <i>What are you doing?</i>

1589
01:32:38,011 --> 01:32:39,054
Just having a cuppa.

1590
01:32:39,138 --> 01:32:40,764
Mom, ask him about the brakes.

1591
01:32:40,848 --> 01:32:43,142
- Go to bed. It's 1 :00 a.m.
- Ask him.

1592
01:32:43,225 --> 01:32:44,685
Go to bed. Now.

1593
01:32:44,768 --> 01:32:46,562
I take it he's not asleep.

1594
01:32:46,645 --> 01:32:48,397
I'm sure he smuggled in a radio.

1595
01:32:48,480 --> 01:32:49,857
<i>Yeah.</i>

1596
01:32:49,940 --> 01:32:51,233
He said to ask, "How are the brakes?"

1597
01:32:51,316 --> 01:32:53,152
The brakes? Yes. No, no, no.

1598
01:32:53,235 --> 01:32:55,320
Tell him they're working for now.

1599
01:32:55,404 --> 01:32:58,073
<i>You know, Shelby's been acting
very strange.</i>

1600
01:32:58,157 --> 01:32:59,283
- <i>Ford have gone...</i>
- Ken.

1601
01:32:59,366 --> 01:33:00,576
<i>...and put up another team.</i>

1602
01:33:00,659 --> 01:33:02,035
- With a GT.
- <i>Ken.</i>

1603
01:33:02,119 --> 01:33:05,456
Some sort of yampy, bloody
corporate test or something, I dunno.

1604
01:33:05,539 --> 01:33:07,583
Just take a rest
whenever you get a chance.

1605
01:33:07,666 --> 01:33:09,001
<i>Sorry, my love, what were you saying?</i>

1606
01:33:09,084 --> 01:33:10,502
You've only got a few hours.

1607
01:33:10,586 --> 01:33:11,754
<i>I can't hear you very well.</i>

1608
01:33:11,837 --> 01:33:13,088
<i>I'm sorry. I can't hear you.</i>

1609
01:33:13,172 --> 01:33:14,381
<i>Wish me luck.</i>

1610
01:33:14,465 --> 01:33:16,133
- Good luck.
- <i>I love you, darling.</i>

1611
01:33:16,800 --> 01:33:19,052
<i>After 23 hours
here at Daytona,</i>

1612
01:33:19,136 --> 01:33:21,472
<i>Walt Hansgen driving
the green and white Ford</i>

1613
01:33:21,555 --> 01:33:25,476
<i>has a commanding lead
over Ken Miles and Shelby American</i>

1614
01:33:25,559 --> 01:33:28,353
<i>as the rest of the field
has fallen off the pace.</i>

1615
01:33:28,437 --> 01:33:29,521
We're locked out.

1616
01:33:29,605 --> 01:33:32,483
Ain't nothing Miles can do
this late in the race.

1617
01:33:33,192 --> 01:33:35,652
Engine's hot. We gotta keep it
under six thou.

1618
01:34:23,367 --> 01:34:24,910
All right.

1619
01:34:50,227 --> 01:34:51,979
She could come apart.

1620
01:34:52,062 --> 01:34:53,438
One way to find out.

1621
01:34:56,567 --> 01:34:58,694
I thought we were keeping him under 6,000?

1622
01:34:59,236 --> 01:35:00,612
Shut up, Don.

1623
01:35:10,205 --> 01:35:12,749
<i>With only minutes
of racing left here at Daytona,</i>

1624
01:35:12,833 --> 01:35:14,793
<i>a pitched battle for the lead
is being waged</i>

1625
01:35:14,877 --> 01:35:17,796
<i>as the number 98 Ford makes
an incredible late surge.</i>

1626
01:35:17,880 --> 01:35:20,007
- What's happening?
- He's moving up.

1627
01:35:20,090 --> 01:35:21,300
COMMENTATOR
<i>...entering the front tri-oval,</i>

1628
01:35:21,383 --> 01:35:23,594
<i>Ken Miles' desperate bid
for the win may prove to be...</i>

1629
01:35:32,227 --> 01:35:33,145
Come on now!

1630
01:35:33,228 --> 01:35:34,938
White flag! Last lap!

1631
01:35:40,611 --> 01:35:42,696
Miles is pushing him. Hard.

1632
01:35:53,373 --> 01:35:54,917
That's it, girl.

1633
01:36:05,802 --> 01:36:09,056
<i>Ken Miles drafts Walt Hansgen
coming into the final turn.</i>

1634
01:36:35,624 --> 01:36:36,667
Come on. Come on.

1635
01:36:40,003 --> 01:36:42,214
What the hell?

1636
01:36:49,972 --> 01:36:51,139
Come on.

1637
01:36:51,598 --> 01:36:52,724
All right.

1638
01:36:57,270 --> 01:36:58,397
Look at this now.

1639
01:37:03,235 --> 01:37:04,403
Damn it!

1640
01:37:12,369 --> 01:37:13,996
Yeah!

1641
01:37:14,079 --> 01:37:16,289
<i>Ken Miles
takes the checkered flag,</i>

1642
01:37:16,373 --> 01:37:18,125
<i>bringing glory to Shelby American.</i>

1643
01:37:21,336 --> 01:37:22,379
How about that?

1644
01:37:32,848 --> 01:37:34,766
Reliability, strength...

1645
01:37:34,850 --> 01:37:35,767
Yes, Leo.

1646
01:37:35,851 --> 01:37:37,644
<i>Mr. Ford, sir, we won.</i>

1647
01:37:38,895 --> 01:37:39,896
Uh-huh.

1648
01:37:39,980 --> 01:37:42,190
We won! Ford won Daytona.

1649
01:37:42,274 --> 01:37:44,026
Hot damn.

1650
01:37:44,109 --> 01:37:45,652
And which team was it, Leo?

1651
01:37:47,195 --> 01:37:49,614
Shelby American. Miles driving.

1652
01:37:51,366 --> 01:37:52,701
Son of a bitch.

1653
01:37:53,702 --> 01:37:55,203
All right.

1654
01:37:55,287 --> 01:37:56,621
Where the hell is he?

1655
01:37:56,705 --> 01:37:58,707
Hang on, I see him. Hey, wait.

1656
01:37:58,790 --> 01:38:00,959
Someone lost a bulldog on the beach.

1657
01:38:02,627 --> 01:38:04,379
No, no. Come on. Come on.

1658
01:38:05,464 --> 01:38:08,633
Come on. Let's go. Let's go.

1659
01:38:08,717 --> 01:38:11,261
Someone get this man a drink.
Someone get him a drink.

1660
01:38:27,152 --> 01:38:28,111
Oi.

1661
01:38:29,279 --> 01:38:31,323
In bed, you. What are you doing?

1662
01:38:32,074 --> 01:38:33,408
Dirty stop out.

1663
01:38:33,950 --> 01:38:34,951
I was...

1664
01:38:35,994 --> 01:38:38,580
drawing a map, so I could
follow you on Le Mans.

1665
01:38:39,206 --> 01:38:40,248
Mmm.

1666
01:38:42,584 --> 01:38:44,252
Look at that.

1667
01:38:45,754 --> 01:38:47,464
That is spot on.

1668
01:38:47,547 --> 01:38:49,549
You are a dab hand, very accurate.

1669
01:38:51,593 --> 01:38:53,095
Tell me about the track.

1670
01:38:53,178 --> 01:38:54,846
No, I can't, Petey.

1671
01:38:54,930 --> 01:38:55,931
Please.

1672
01:39:04,815 --> 01:39:06,733
Well, you start at the start line.

1673
01:39:07,567 --> 01:39:09,486
Yeah, but you actually start here

1674
01:39:09,569 --> 01:39:11,571
because you have to run
to your car at Le Mans.

1675
01:39:11,655 --> 01:39:13,073
True enough.

1676
01:39:13,156 --> 01:39:16,284
So, once your old man manages
to hobble over...

1677
01:39:17,035 --> 01:39:19,412
- and pull out...
- And not hit anyone.

1678
01:39:19,496 --> 01:39:21,414
Yes, right.

1679
01:39:22,290 --> 01:39:25,752
Then you accelerate very hard
up to Dunlop Bridge...

1680
01:39:26,753 --> 01:39:28,672
road banking away from ya

1681
01:39:28,755 --> 01:39:31,591
and down through the trees to the Esses...

1682
01:39:31,675 --> 01:39:33,802
and accelerate up to Tertre Rouge.

1683
01:39:33,885 --> 01:39:35,929
Critical first gear corner.

1684
01:39:36,596 --> 01:39:37,806
Fast entry.

1685
01:39:38,306 --> 01:39:40,851
Keep your speed up for your exit onto...

1686
01:39:42,018 --> 01:39:43,186
Mulsanne.

1687
01:39:43,812 --> 01:39:46,565
Long straightaway, hemmed in by poplars.

1688
01:39:46,648 --> 01:39:49,734
Top gear, 210 miles per hour.

1689
01:39:50,193 --> 01:39:52,320
And down to third, revs up.

1690
01:39:52,404 --> 01:39:53,780
Revs are your friend.

1691
01:39:54,698 --> 01:39:58,201
Get a maximum exit. Let the car run free.

1692
01:39:58,285 --> 01:40:00,203
Over the brow...

1693
01:40:00,287 --> 01:40:01,371
then wham!

1694
01:40:03,039 --> 01:40:04,374
Mulsanne Corner.

1695
01:40:04,457 --> 01:40:07,085
Accelerate to Arnage

1696
01:40:07,169 --> 01:40:08,670
and then over the rise to the White House.

1697
01:40:08,753 --> 01:40:10,630
You get that right and...

1698
01:40:14,009 --> 01:40:16,094
Your first three and a half minutes...

1699
01:40:17,220 --> 01:40:18,638
of 24 hours.

1700
01:40:19,931 --> 01:40:26,396
But... you can't make every lap perfect.

1701
01:40:27,480 --> 01:40:28,899
But I can try.

1702
01:40:34,738 --> 01:40:36,072
All right.

1703
01:40:37,115 --> 01:40:38,450
Off to bed, you.

1704
01:40:41,203 --> 01:40:43,914
I will... wake you...

1705
01:40:45,040 --> 01:40:46,333
before I leave for France.

1706
01:40:47,167 --> 01:40:48,168
I promise.

1707
01:40:48,668 --> 01:40:50,837
Okay. Good night.

1708
01:41:18,740 --> 01:41:20,116
Eh, where's, um...

1709
01:41:20,992 --> 01:41:23,745
Where's that? The Hotel Saint Pierre?

1710
01:41:25,163 --> 01:41:26,456
Where?

1711
01:42:12,794 --> 01:42:14,587
It's gonna rain again tomorrow.

1712
01:42:20,010 --> 01:42:21,553
There's always rain here.

1713
01:42:25,015 --> 01:42:26,599
Start'll be dry though,

1714
01:42:26,683 --> 01:42:29,853
so we'll swap out your tires come rain.

1715
01:42:32,522 --> 01:42:33,940
Yeah.

1716
01:42:36,359 --> 01:42:40,613
Might be smart to sleep, Bulldog.

1717
01:42:42,657 --> 01:42:44,159
Well, you, too.

1718
01:42:44,951 --> 01:42:46,077
I'm not driving.

1719
01:42:48,955 --> 01:42:52,083
That's a bloody shame, that.

1720
01:42:52,459 --> 01:42:54,210
Oh, hell, I couldn't make this team.

1721
01:42:59,466 --> 01:43:01,301
I'm gonna go walk the first corner.

1722
01:43:03,261 --> 01:43:04,763
I figured.

1723
01:43:15,648 --> 01:43:16,775
Counting on it.

1724
01:43:51,643 --> 01:43:52,936
Ken.

1725
01:43:53,019 --> 01:43:54,354
Chaz.

1726
01:44:00,026 --> 01:44:01,194
We'll change
the color of them seats,

1727
01:44:01,277 --> 01:44:02,278
shall we, Frost?

1728
01:44:08,451 --> 01:44:10,662
Well, if this were
a beauty pageant...

1729
01:44:11,204 --> 01:44:12,622
we just lost.

1730
01:44:13,790 --> 01:44:14,874
Looks fast, don't it?

1731
01:44:14,958 --> 01:44:17,335
Ah, looks aren't everything.

1732
01:44:21,589 --> 01:44:24,467
Scarfiotti and Bandini start for Ferrari.

1733
01:44:30,306 --> 01:44:31,558
You can take him.

1734
01:44:31,641 --> 01:44:33,893
Four minutes, Ken.
Four minutes, buddy.

1735
01:44:33,977 --> 01:44:35,228
<i>Live from Le Mans, France.</i>

1736
01:44:35,311 --> 01:44:37,439
Mom! Come on.

1737
01:44:37,522 --> 01:44:39,107
All right, coming.

1738
01:44:39,941 --> 01:44:42,485
<i>The 24 Hours of Le Mans.</i>

1739
01:44:42,569 --> 01:44:44,070
<i>And there are the cars lined up...</i>

1740
01:44:47,157 --> 01:44:49,159
<i>Drivers,
please take your places.</i>

1741
01:45:08,136 --> 01:45:09,137
- <i>And there they are...</i>
- There he is.

1742
01:45:09,220 --> 01:45:10,680
<i>...lined up, ready to go.</i>

1743
01:45:10,763 --> 01:45:12,182
<i>They're lined up
as per their practice times.</i>

1744
01:45:12,265 --> 01:45:13,475
<i>Faster cars are up to our left.</i>

1745
01:46:04,817 --> 01:46:06,819
Oh, bloody joker!

1746
01:46:12,283 --> 01:46:14,536
<i>Number 10, a Bizzarrini,
almost loses control.</i>

1747
01:46:15,203 --> 01:46:16,663
It's all right.

1748
01:46:19,165 --> 01:46:20,708
You looked great out there, sir.

1749
01:46:21,834 --> 01:46:23,169
What happened to Miles?

1750
01:46:31,886 --> 01:46:33,721
Bloody hell.

1751
01:46:35,390 --> 01:46:36,558
No.

1752
01:46:43,273 --> 01:46:45,149
Poxy bastard.

1753
01:47:21,019 --> 01:47:24,897
<i>After one lap,
Bandini-Ferrari is in first place.</i>

1754
01:47:28,693 --> 01:47:30,361
Where is Miles?

1755
01:47:32,572 --> 01:47:34,616
- Where the hell is Ken?
- I don't know.

1756
01:47:43,750 --> 01:47:44,751
He's coming in.

1757
01:47:44,834 --> 01:47:45,960
Oi! He's coming in.

1758
01:47:46,044 --> 01:47:47,170
He's coming in. Let's go.

1759
01:47:47,253 --> 01:47:48,755
Frosty, come on. Let's go. Move it.

1760
01:47:49,422 --> 01:47:51,049
I think it's his door.

1761
01:47:51,132 --> 01:47:53,134
<i>That's a rough start
for the Ford team so early...</i>

1762
01:47:56,679 --> 01:47:59,891
The bloody door won't close!

1763
01:47:59,974 --> 01:48:02,101
All right. All right.
We'll take care of it.

1764
01:48:02,185 --> 01:48:03,436
Come on, guys.

1765
01:48:03,519 --> 01:48:04,646
Damn door!

1766
01:48:05,229 --> 01:48:06,648
- Try that.
- This'll do it.

1767
01:48:06,731 --> 01:48:08,066
Shelby, what the hell is wrong?

1768
01:48:08,733 --> 01:48:09,817
Something's hitting the frame.

1769
01:48:09,901 --> 01:48:11,778
Oh, you're joking, aren't ya?

1770
01:48:12,528 --> 01:48:14,113
Guys, get outta the way.

1771
01:48:14,197 --> 01:48:15,531
Just get outta the way. Hold it.

1772
01:48:17,075 --> 01:48:19,077
Go! Go, go, go!

1773
01:48:27,043 --> 01:48:27,960
He's back out.

1774
01:48:28,044 --> 01:48:29,045
