2076
02:15:03,263 --> 02:15:05,848
Yeah! Yeah!

2077
02:15:12,480 --> 02:15:13,898
Look at that.

2078
02:15:16,317 --> 02:15:17,860
- Well done, Leo.
- You too, Don.

2079
02:15:35,169 --> 02:15:36,421
<i>Please stand by.</i>

2080
02:15:36,504 --> 02:15:38,172
<i>Final results are under review.</i>

2081
02:15:38,256 --> 02:15:40,258
...is explain to me
how he's finished first

2082
02:15:40,341 --> 02:15:41,634
and he's not won the race?

2083
02:15:41,718 --> 02:15:43,886
Because McLaren
started from further,

2084
02:15:43,970 --> 02:15:45,430
so he came in... see, he won.

2085
02:15:45,513 --> 02:15:46,597
Look, it's not a tie.

2086
02:15:46,681 --> 02:15:47,765
No, because McLaren...

2087
02:15:47,849 --> 02:15:49,309
Because McLaren started further back,

2088
02:15:49,392 --> 02:15:50,977
he's saying he's traveled
that little bit further,

2089
02:15:51,060 --> 02:15:52,478
so he's won and not Ken.

2090
02:15:52,562 --> 02:15:54,439
That is bullshit. That's bullshit.

2091
02:15:54,522 --> 02:15:56,357
Shel! Hold on!

2092
02:16:10,413 --> 02:16:12,081
- Where's the tie?
- Hey, hey, hey.

2093
02:16:12,165 --> 02:16:13,333
Where's the goddamn tie?

2094
02:16:13,416 --> 02:16:14,500
What?

2095
02:16:14,584 --> 02:16:15,918
- You son of a bitch!
- Hey, Shelby!

2096
02:16:16,002 --> 02:16:17,378
- You knew!
- No, I didn't know!

2097
02:16:17,462 --> 02:16:19,464
- That's enough! Enough!
- Get off me! Hey!

2098
02:16:20,131 --> 02:16:21,716
Bruce.

2099
02:16:21,799 --> 02:16:23,509
Nice race, mate. Congrats.

2100
02:16:45,448 --> 02:16:46,741
Shel!

2101
02:16:51,287 --> 02:16:52,747
They robbed you, Ken.

2102
02:16:52,830 --> 02:16:54,582
<i>Here is the clarification.</i>

2103
02:16:54,665 --> 02:16:57,168
<i>Though the drivers finished
the race in a heat,</i>

2104
02:16:57,251 --> 02:17:00,797
<i>McLaren has been ruled the winner
as he started from farther back.</i>

2105
02:17:00,880 --> 02:17:02,632
Some bullshit technicality.

2106
02:17:02,715 --> 02:17:06,511
<i>Final results. Ford number 2,
driven by McLaren and Amon,</i>

2107
02:17:06,594 --> 02:17:08,054
<i>is the winner.</i>

2108
02:17:08,137 --> 02:17:12,058
<i>Ford number 1, driven by Miles and Hulme,
second place.</i>

2109
02:17:12,141 --> 02:17:16,270
<i>In third place, Bucknum and Hutcherson
in Ford number 5.</i>

2110
02:17:16,354 --> 02:17:17,605
I never should've asked you.

2111
02:17:23,986 --> 02:17:25,530
Selling cars, huh?

2112
02:17:28,408 --> 02:17:29,742
That's what they do.

2113
02:17:30,952 --> 02:17:33,996
Well, you promised me the drive.

2114
02:17:36,916 --> 02:17:38,042
Not the win.

2115
02:17:39,335 --> 02:17:40,753
It was a hell of a drive.

2116
02:17:41,921 --> 02:17:43,423
She's a hell of a machine.

2117
02:17:44,215 --> 02:17:45,591
Oh, she's fast.

2118
02:17:47,427 --> 02:17:48,803
Could be faster.

2119
02:17:50,763 --> 02:17:52,140
The 7 liter's sweet...

2120
02:17:52,807 --> 02:17:54,016
but, uh...

2121
02:17:55,101 --> 02:17:56,894
we still need a lighter chassis.

2122
02:17:56,978 --> 02:18:00,731
I was thinking bonded aluminium.

2123
02:18:00,815 --> 02:18:03,609
It's a ground-up rebuild,
but if it works...

2124
02:18:04,360 --> 02:18:06,529
we can lose a couple hundred pounds.

2125
02:18:06,612 --> 02:18:08,322
Well, what the hell are we doing here?

2126
02:18:10,032 --> 02:18:11,993
Let me take a shower, get a cup of tea...

2127
02:18:12,702 --> 02:18:14,245
ham and cheese cob or something.

2128
02:18:15,204 --> 02:18:16,998
We're gonna get
the bastards next year.

2129
02:18:41,022 --> 02:18:43,399
Got a bit of fuel left in the tank.

2130
02:18:44,734 --> 02:18:46,611
What do you think
of those honeycomb panels?

2131
02:18:46,694 --> 02:18:48,237
What you were looking for?

2132
02:18:48,696 --> 02:18:49,864
Don't know yet.

2133
02:19:15,598 --> 02:19:17,225
She looks pretty good.

2134
02:19:27,527 --> 02:19:31,072
<i>There's a point at 7,000 RPM...</i>

2135
02:19:32,448 --> 02:19:34,450
<i>where everything fades.</i>

2136
02:19:37,078 --> 02:19:39,330
<i>The machine becomes weightless.</i>

2137
02:19:40,456 --> 02:19:41,582
<i>Just disappears.</i>

2138
02:19:42,500 --> 02:19:43,584
Yeah!

2139
02:19:43,668 --> 02:19:44,752
<i>And all that's left</i>

2140
02:19:44,835 --> 02:19:45,920
<i>is a body...</i>

2141
02:19:46,003 --> 02:19:47,713
<i>moving through space and time.</i>

2142
02:19:51,300 --> 02:19:53,344
<i>7,000 RPM.</i>

2143
02:19:54,512 --> 02:19:55,763
<i>That's where you meet it.</i>

2144
02:19:58,057 --> 02:19:59,725
<i>You feel it coming.</i>

2145
02:19:59,809 --> 02:20:01,852
<i>It creeps up on you, close in your ear.</i>

2146
02:20:10,319 --> 02:20:11,779
<i>Asks you a question.</i>

2147
02:20:13,072 --> 02:20:14,740
<i>The only question that matters.</i>

2148
02:20:20,788 --> 02:20:21,872
Get the van!

2149
02:20:23,332 --> 02:20:24,709
<i>"Who are you?"</i>

2150
02:20:58,451 --> 02:20:59,619
What do you think?

2151
02:20:59,702 --> 02:21:02,038
It's fantastic. Feels really good.

2152
02:21:02,830 --> 02:21:04,040
Nice and smooth.

2153
02:21:05,166 --> 02:21:07,168
No vibration in the box.
Feels really strong.

2154
02:21:07,251 --> 02:21:09,211
You drove it for less than an hour.

2155
02:21:09,795 --> 02:21:11,756
You can't tell shit after an hour.

2156
02:21:11,839 --> 02:21:15,217
Go for seven even, that'd be 14 all in.

2157
02:21:15,301 --> 02:21:16,427
Hey, Shel.

2158
02:21:26,520 --> 02:21:29,607
Hey, Shel, that guy,
you know the one in the hat,

2159
02:21:29,690 --> 02:21:32,276
