2160
02:21:32,360 --> 02:21:34,654
His and hers. Full freight.

2161
02:21:35,655 --> 02:21:38,157
They, uh, flew in from Galveston.

2162
02:21:38,240 --> 02:21:39,408
Uh-huh.

2163
02:21:40,868 --> 02:21:44,747
Uh, I need you to come outside
for maybe a minute.

2164
02:21:45,706 --> 02:21:46,874
And do what?

2165
02:21:48,709 --> 02:21:50,002
Be Carroll Shelby.

2166
02:21:51,253 --> 02:21:53,422
Tell them a story, spin a few magic words.

2167
02:21:54,590 --> 02:21:57,218
What does that mean? "Magic words"?

2168
02:21:58,511 --> 02:21:59,595
It means...

2169
02:22:00,179 --> 02:22:02,223
come outside and say hello

2170
02:22:02,306 --> 02:22:04,350
and make them feel good
about their purchase.

2171
02:22:04,433 --> 02:22:05,726
They're getting the damn cars.

2172
02:22:05,810 --> 02:22:07,478
That's what they get
for their money, Phil.

2173
02:22:07,561 --> 02:22:09,230
Now, either they want 'em or they don't.

2174
02:22:09,313 --> 02:22:11,232
- Am I some kind of a lounge act?
- No.

2175
02:22:11,315 --> 02:22:12,566
Am I here to talk people into things?

2176
02:22:24,286 --> 02:22:26,038
It's been six months, Shel.

2177
02:22:27,498 --> 02:22:29,375
Six months.

2178
02:22:33,671 --> 02:22:35,881
Sometimes they don't
get out of the car.

2179
02:23:11,375 --> 02:23:12,585
Peter!

2180
02:23:13,711 --> 02:23:16,255
Peter, come and take the garbage out.

2181
02:23:16,338 --> 02:23:17,590
Mr. Shelby.

2182
02:23:19,258 --> 02:23:20,509
Oh, hello, Pete.

2183
02:23:22,678 --> 02:23:24,138
I remember that wrench.

2184
02:23:25,431 --> 02:23:27,057
My dad threw it at you.

2185
02:23:28,517 --> 02:23:29,643
I believe he did.

2186
02:23:30,686 --> 02:23:31,854
Why?

2187
02:23:34,648 --> 02:23:35,775
Oh.

2188
02:23:36,859 --> 02:23:38,986
I think I probably said something to him.

2189
02:23:39,987 --> 02:23:41,363
Called him a few names.

2190
02:23:43,616 --> 02:23:44,909
That's right.

2191
02:23:53,793 --> 02:23:55,211
Do you wanna speak to my mum?

2192
02:23:56,128 --> 02:23:58,088
Well, I did. Uh...

2193
02:23:58,964 --> 02:24:00,925
I came to say hello,
check in on her and...

2194
02:24:05,846 --> 02:24:07,723
Then I started thinking that sometimes...

2195
02:24:10,518 --> 02:24:12,645
uh, words...

2196
02:24:13,354 --> 02:24:17,191
just... are-- are not useful.

2197
02:24:23,239 --> 02:24:25,533
Tools are useful 'cause
you can make stuff with 'em

2198
02:24:25,616 --> 02:24:27,326
and you can fix stuff with 'em.

2199
02:24:28,828 --> 02:24:30,287
Here.

2200
02:24:31,205 --> 02:24:32,331
Thanks.

2201
02:24:41,173 --> 02:24:42,633
Your daddy was, uh...

2202
02:24:46,220 --> 02:24:47,972
He was your friend.

2203
02:24:54,019 --> 02:24:55,187
Yes, he was.

2204
02:24:56,689 --> 02:24:58,232
Yes, sir.

2205
02:25:03,153 --> 02:25:05,573
And he thought you was
just finer than frog fur.

2206
02:25:10,828 --> 02:25:12,329
Peter!

2207
02:25:17,209 --> 02:25:19,169
I think I've gotta go help my mum.

2208
02:25:21,547 --> 02:25:23,883
What are you doing here then? Go on.

2209
02:25:24,925 --> 02:25:26,260
Bye.
